commit_message:
Trim reads to common length (30bp), update reaper

Updated reaper requires explicitly specifying “@” in front of read ID
Use proper path settings for tools
Fix bug in LSF job condition
Update to match format of tRNA annotation
Allow to specify log and result folder in config
Local modification to run last step
Local modifications to run prelimiary version
Add possibility of using absolute read data path

Bugfix and error reporting improvement

* Fixed a bug where the `toolpath` variable was overwritten
* Fixed the FastQ format output from `reaper`
* Fixed output path of `sort-and-index`
* Fixed paths of project config paths
* Improved diagnostic output from pipeline
Fix: tools should be machine agnostic

QC reporting added

Running the pipeline now works in principle, even if some of the tools
still need to be implemented and logging needs to be improved.
Pipeline reads input files from config
Stub for sort-and-index, reorganised tool paths

Reorganise environment setup

Make loading config values more general so that individual tools can use
the mechanism transparently for their own configuration.
Put config parsing into module to ease debugging
